    <stitle>SINGLE REDUCTION, TANDEM AXLES: SPICER J400-S, W460-S - REMOVE - DIFFERENTIAL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="6">
        <title>DIFFERENTIAL</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove cotter pins and locks from bearing caps (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400415">Figure 15</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400415" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400415" filename="../figg14/g1400415.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Remove Cotter Pins and Locks From Bearing Caps</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Match mark one differential bearing cap and leg of carrier with center punch or chisel for
                correct reassembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400416">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400416" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400416" filename="../figg14/g1400416.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Match Mark Differential Bearing Cap and Leg of Carrier</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen 4 (four) bearing cap retaining bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400417">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400417" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400417" filename="../figg14/g1400417.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Loosen Bearing Cap Retaining Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen adjusting rings, relieving bearing preload (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400418">Figure 18</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400418" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400418" filename="../figg14/g1400418.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Loosen Adjusting Rings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 4 (four) bearing cap retaining bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove adjusting rings.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove bearing caps (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400419">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400419" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400419" filename="../figg14/g1400419.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Remove Bearing Caps</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Carefully lift the ring gear and differential subassembly out of carrier (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400420">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400420" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400420" filename="../figg14/g1400420.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. Lift Ring Gear and Differential Subassembly Out of Carrier</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The ring gear side of subassembly must be tipped up for the ring gear to clear pinion roller
                        bearing retainer.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Use care while removing subassembly to avoid damaging the ring and pinion gears and A></para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
